transcript.text: Hi everyone!
Today I will show you this makeup look
that I created with the Naked Heat from UD
It's the first time that I am using this palette
I have bought it during a flash sale
on the sephora website in July
I had never used it
because I wanted to use it first
in this video
First of all, it's a palette
that contains mostly warm shades inside
And what I liked a lot it's that
in comparison to other Naked palettes
most of the shades are matte (and I prefer)
only 5 shades are shimmery
First good point to me
I love warm shades
I guess I own a ton of warm palettes already
At the end of the video I will suggest you some dupes
and share you my thoughts about the palette
First I put black pencil on my waterline
down
and up
Now I put it on my lower lash line
to start the base of my makeup
and smudge it as always
I take the shade Ashes
with a flat brush
and put it over the black base
I put a black pencil because I wanted something pretty dark
I blend it with the shade En Fuego
with a little round brush
I put the color very down
and thick
Now lids
with Oxblood pencil from NYX
I create a shape that I like a lot
I do this very often
It's a smoky with a light point in the center
I put the pencil where I want to put my darkest color
inner and outer corners
and don't forget to smudge!
I put some in my crease too
It doesn't need to be perfect it's just supposed
to help with the shape
BUT smudge a lot
because if you don't you will get some color difference
when applying you shadows
Before continuing the lid work, I apply Ounce on my brow bone
to help me blend after
I take again En Fuego
and apply it over the pencil shape
And I blend in the crease with the shade He Devil
I blend with some circle movements
and work it until I like the result
it has to be very smoked
Don't be afraid to go far with your brush
That way you will get a beautiful blending
Time for the light point
I use Scorched
one of the shiny shades
Prefer shiny shades for your light points
I apply it with my fingertip
because it gives more intensity
I blend it with the other shades
To finish my shadow work
I apply the shade Slumber on my inner corner
I can draw my eyeliner now
I start from the middle
I apply it at the very lash line
I go to the inner corner little by little
It has to be very thin in inner corner
To dray the end keep your eyes open
look straight
draw a straight line for the direction
and thicken it until you like
I want to add glitters on my inner corner
I use this glitter liner from LASplash
and put a bit
I wanna apply falsies so first mascara
it's Lash Alert from Eyeko
it's not cakey
and will put my lashes right after
I  lately like Sagittarius from Black Moon
I first apply some glue
the House of Lashes glue is truly the best on earth
I use the black one here
I like applying them with my lash tweezer
I wait a bit for the glue to be dry
My eyes are done, so now I do my lips
with Elle from Lime crime
with Cosmic Metal from NYX on top
shade Speed of Light
This makeup is finished, I hope you enjoyed it
My thoughts about the palette are
the pigmentation is good
application and blending are easy
nothing to say about the quality
The range of color is very trendy lately
It costs 49€
I know it's a budget
You can buy it at Sephora with some discounts
I had 20% when I purchased it
I wanted to suggest you some dupes
I have 2 palettes for small budgets
they come from NYX
First is the NYX Ultimate
Warm Neutrals palette
To me it's THE ONE that look a LOT like the Naked Heat one
the shades are very similar
Here are the two side by side
From NYX too
the new Perfect Filter palette
it's the Rustic Antique one
there are less shades but very similar
Trendy version but not less expensive
the Holy Grail from Violet Voss
I have two palettes for pro alternative

35OS & 35OM

This video is finished see you in my next one !
